[[Page - 48]]

KING
We knew your taste for curious quips,
For cranks and contradictions queer;
And with the laughter on our lips,
We wished you there to hear.
We said, "If we could tell it him,
How Frederic would the joke enjoy!"
And so we've risked both life and limb
To tell it to our boy.
Twill be our death that paradox
We've quips and quibbles heard in flocks
But none to beat that paradox
Ha, ha, ha, ha. Ho, ho, ho, ho.

RUTH
This is the jest and when unfurled
The truth of what we say 'twill show
You came into this wicked world
Just one and twenty years ago
But though since you by me were nursed
Years twenty one have passed away
You have not seen the twenty first
Recurrence of your natal day.

FRED
'Twill be our death that paradox.
(puzzled.)
Now let me see how that can be
I'm twenty one that's very clear
Moreover it is plain to me
Man has birthday once a year
To solve this quip I see no way
All common sense the statement mocks
I beg of you without delay
Explain this startling paradox. [[29]]

FRED
(interested).
That paradox?

