## FINALE - Hymn to the Nobility.

GENERAL
Let foreigners look down with scorn
On legislators heaven-born;
We know what limpid wisdom runs
From Peers and all their eldest sons.
Enwrapped the true-born Briton hears
The wisdom of his House of Peers.

SERGEANT
And if a noble lord should die
And leave no near progeny,
His twentieth cousin takes his place
And legislates with equal grace.

RUTH
But should a son and heir survive,
Or other nearer relative,
Then twentieth cousins get you hence -
You're persons of no consequence.
